      • alert

        public static GetAlertSupplier alert​(java.util.function.Predicate<org.openqa.selenium.Alert> criteria,
                                     java.time.Duration duration,
                                     java.time.Duration sleeping,
                                     java.util.function.Supplier<? extends org.openqa.selenium.NoAlertPresentException> supplier)
        This method builds a function which waits for alert, checks the result by criteria and returns it.
        Parameters:
        criteria - used to check the found alert
        duration - of the waiting for alert
        sleeping - time for the sleeping between attempts to get the desired result.
        supplier - which returns the exception to be thrown when alert that suits criteria is not found and time is expired.
        Returns:
        a function which waits for alert, checks the result by criteria and returns it or throws NoAlertPresentException when alert is not appear or it doesn't suit the criteria.
